 <text>
  <front>
   <head>RURAL SIMPLICITY. AN ODE.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">O Thou, whom Love and Fancy lead</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To wander near this woodland hill,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">If ever music sooth'd thy quill,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Or pity wak'd thy gentle reed,</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Repose beneath my humble tree,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">If thou lov'st Simplicity.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Stranger, if thy lot has laid</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In toilsome scenes of busy life,</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Full sorely may'st thou see the strife</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Of weary passions ill repaid,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In a garden live like me,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">If thou lov'st Simplicity.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Flowers have sprung for many a year</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">O'er the village-maiden's grave,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That, one memorial-sprig to save,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Bore it from a sister's bier;</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And homeward walking, wept o'er me</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The true tears of Simplicity.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And soon, her cottage-window near,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With care my slender stem she plac'd,</l>
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And fondly thus her Grief embrac'd,</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And cherish'd sad Remembrance dear;</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For Love sincere and Friendship free</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Are children of Simplicity.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="25" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When past was many a painful day,</l>
     <l n="26" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Slow-pacing o'er the village-green</l>
     <l n="27" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In white were all its maidens seen,</l>
     <l n="28" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And bore my guardian friend away.</l>
     <l n="29" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Ah, Death! what sacrifice to thee</l>
     <l n="30" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The ruins of Simplicity!</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="6" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="31" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">One generous swain her heart approv'd,</l>
     <l n="32" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A youth, whose fond and faithful breast.</l>
     <l n="33" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With many an artless sigh confest,</l>
     <l n="34" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In Nature's language that he lov'd:</l>
     <l n="35" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But, Stranger, 'tis no tale for thee,</l>
     <l n="36" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Unless thou lov'st Simplicity.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="7" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="37" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">He died — and soon her lip was cold,</l>
     <l n="38" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And soon her rosy lip was pale,</l>
     <l n="39" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The village wept to hear the tale</l>
     <l n="40" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When for both the slow bell toll'd —</l>
     <l n="41" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Beneath yon flowery turf they lie,</l>
     <l n="42" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The lovers of Simplicity.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="8" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="43" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Yet one boon have I to crave;</l>
     <l n="44" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Stranger, if thy pity bleed,</l>
     <l n="45" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Wilt thou do one tender deed,</l>
     <l n="46" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And strew my pale flowers o'er their grave?</l>
     <l n="47" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">So lightly lie the turf on thee,</l>
     <l n="48" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Because thou lov'st Simplicity!</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
